  <fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="Building Digital Twin">Building Digital Twin</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
<html:p>3D-reconstruction is not <html:strong>actionable</html:strong> i.e. we can reconstruct a room with a cup but if you try to lift the cup the whole image moves (cup is attached to counter).</html:p>

<html:p><fr:link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.15278" type="external">Drawer</fr:link></html:p>
<html:ol><html:li>Anchor gaussians around the zero level-set</html:li>
<html:li>Scene decomposition. Identify interactable and actionable objects</html:li>
<html:li>Use LLM for reasoning over objects i.e. density, types of joints</html:li>
<html:li>Recover invisible regions via differentiable rendering + generative modeling</html:li></html:ol>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="Learning From Humans">Learning From Humans</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
<html:p>Real-to-sim-to-real: record environment -&gt; build simulation of environment -&gt; train in simulator -&gt; deploy in real world.</html:p>
<html:p>Ideas:</html:p>
<html:ol><html:li>Object state as an anchor</html:li>
  <html:ul><html:li>Get rid of human.</html:li>
    <html:li>Find corresponding actions that match object states in trajectory.</html:li></html:ul>
  <html:li>Still not robust for precise movements.</html:li>
  <html:li>Test-time alignment</html:li>
  <html:ul><html:li>Unroll in real world</html:li>
    <html:li>Replay in simulation</html:li>
    <html:li>Align</html:li></html:ul></html:ol>
<html:p>RL -&gt; Imitation Learning</html:p>
<html:ol><html:li>Do imitation learning on noisy trajectories.</html:li>
  <html:li>Use noisy robot <html:strong>and</html:strong> human trajectories</html:li>
  <html:li>Use classifier to try to predict whether trajectory is human or robot</html:li>
  <html:ul><html:li>Noise here is the end noise in the diffusion training phase.</html:li>
    <html:li>Only use indistinguishable trajectories.</html:li></html:ul></html:ol>
<html:p>Upshot is that they can "augment" robot data with human data in the diffusion training phase by including human trajectories when sampling high noise.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
